Xi calls for opening up the economy to the wider world
It is necessary to open the economy to the wider world to boost growth, President Xi Jinping told the group, whose task is to reform management on Tuesday.
"China should engage in attracting foreign investment and expertise and improve open policies," he said, referring to the 16th meeting of the central leadership group for deepening overall reform.
The promotion of openness in the face of emerging reforms will provide a new impetus and vitality, and will also provide a new space for economic growth, Xi said.
The Steering Group adopted a number of directives, including a negative regulatory list of market access, the release of border control policies, State Enterprise Support (SOE) to absorb private capital and the reorganisation of the resident registration system.
The statement states that a negative list will be drawn up identifying sectors and enterprises that are outside the investment limits.
This system will be gradually tested and improved through testing programs.
This step is significant because it will give the market a greater role in allocating resources, ensuring a legal business environment and making the market more open, the statement said.
The government will also release controls on the powers it delegates to companies, and make sure that companies themselves decide how to run their businesses.
The statement also states that China will enable border regions to discover new models of cross-border economic cooperation and new mechanisms to support regional growth.
In an effort to open up the state-controlled sector, more areas will be opened up to private investment.
“The government will not change its policy towards foreign investment and will protect the legitimate interests of companies that are financed from abroad and will provide them with better services,” the statement said.
In addition, it will be easier for foreigners to apply for a permanent residence permit or a "green card," thanks to the optimization of requirements and simplification of the application process.
Ensuring the rights of lawyers to practice and develop professional judges and prosecutors was also discussed at the meeting.
The meeting was also attended by Premier Li Keqiang and leaders Liu Yunshan and Zhang Gaoli, according to a statement issued after the meeting.
